1 (3) Single family residential units such as:
2 (A) condominiums;
3 (B) townhouses;
4 (C) manufactured homes; or
5 (D) homes in a subdivision;
6 when sold, leased, or otherwise conveyed on a unit-by-unit
7 basis, even if those units are part of a larger building or parcel
8 or are located on real estate containing more than four (4)
9 residential units.
10 Sec. 3. (a) As used in this chapter, "commercial property
11 services contract" means a contract that:
12 (1) is initially entered into by a service provider and a
13 property owner after June 30, 2026; and
14 (2) provides for the provision of:
15 (A) services; and
16 (B) any personal property related to providing, or
17 necessary to provide, those services;
18 with respect to the property owner's commercial property.
19 (b) The term includes a contract for:
20 (1) private waste hauling or removal services;
21 (2) security or alarm services;
22 (3) services involving fire prevention or suppression systems,
23 including any related inspection or maintenance services;
24 (4) document shredding services;
25 (5) landscaping or irrigation services;
26 (6) cleaning or sanitation services; or
27 (7) other similar services;
28 used in a commercial operation.
29 Sec. 4. As used in this chapter, "person" means an individual, a
30 partnership, a limited liability company, a corporation, an
31 association, or any other legal entity.
32 Sec. 5. As used in this chapter, "property owner" means a
33 person that:
34 (1) owns, controls, or manages commercial property; and
35 (2) is authorized to enter into a commercial property services
36 contract with respect to the commercial property.
37 Sec. 6. As used in this chapter, "service provider" means a
38 person that agrees to provide:
39 (1) services; and
40 (2) any personal property related to providing, or necessary
41 to provide, those services;
42 with respect to commercial property, under a commercial property
